HEADWORD: Lithy
<hw>Lith"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Lithe</er>.]</ety> <def>Easily bent; pliable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lithy tree</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a European
shrub (<spn>Viburnum Lantana</spn>); -- so named from its tough and
flexible stem.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
